   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The transport units must be at the installation location before
starting the assembly. After transport units have been attached, they
can no longer be moved unless separated.</p>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">When attaching two transport units a total
of ten fastening sets are needed. For the frame six fastening sets
are needed , three at the front <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A)</b> and three at the back <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(B)</b> and for the socket four fastening sets, two at the front <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(C)</b> and two at the back <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(D)</b>.</p>
            <note class="- topic/note ">The shown attachment
locations for the frame, <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A)</b> and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(B)</b>, are only approximate
and will depend on where the traverses are placed in the system.</note>
